{"lemma":"عَقَبَةٍ","slug":"عَقَبَةٍ","root":"ع.ق.ب","root_slug":"ع-ق-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ق-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَقَبَة","root":"عقب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29826","n29837","n29838","n29839"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"that remains as a last in a row of succession"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"time, turn, instance in which something occurs in succession"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alternative form of عُقْب (ʕuqb, “consequence, result, issue”)","tags":["alt-of","alternative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"obstacle, hindrance, difficulty, handicap, hurdle"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pass, steep mountain road"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕuq.ba/","/ʕa.qa.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29826","headword_ar":"عَقَبَهُ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqobN","text_ar":"عَقْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TK,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He struck his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqib","text_ar":"عَقِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqabahu","text_ar":"عَقَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqobN","text_ar":"عَقْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuquwbN","text_ar":"عُقُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came after him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at his heel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence, properly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"close after him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but often meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near after him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, Mgh, Msb, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"followed him; succeeded him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took, his place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEqbhu","text_ar":"اعقبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K, TA:) and in like manner both are said of anything, (TA,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eq~bhu","text_ar":"عقّبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEoqiybN","text_ar":"تَعْقِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EAqbhu","text_ar":"عاقبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEtqbhu","text_ar":"اعتقبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it came after;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb, K, * TA;) &c., as above: (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEq~bhu","text_ar":"تعقّبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in this sense, but not rightly. (Mgh.) [All primarily denote proximate sequence.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqabuwnaA","text_ar":"عَقَبُونَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqabuwA mino xalofinaA","text_ar":"عَقَبُوا مِنْ خَلْفِنَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They came after us."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqabuwnaA mino xalofinaA","text_ar":"عَقَبُونَا مِنْ خَلْفِنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaq~abuwnaA","text_ar":"عَقَّبُونَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They succeeded us, in alighting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking up their abode, after our departure."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEid~apu taEoqubu AlT~alaAqa","text_ar":"العِدَّةُ تَعْقُبُ الطَّلَاقَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eid~ap","text_ar":"عِدَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"follows divorce."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonuhu","text_ar":"ا@بْنُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba fulaAnN faA^aEoqabahu","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ فُلَانٌ فَاَعْقَبَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqabahu","text_ar":"عَقَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one went away, and his son succeeded him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took his place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEqb","text_ar":"اعقب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This succeeded this"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said when the latter is gone, and there remains nothing of it, and the former has taken its place. (TA.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqaba","text_ar":"عَقَبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN makaAna A^abiyhi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ مَكَانَ اَبِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqobN","text_ar":"عَقْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and quasi-inf. n. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAqibapN","text_ar":"عَاقِبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", this being a subst. used in the sense of an inf. n., like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA*ibapN","text_ar":"كَاذِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [said to be] in the Kur lvi. 2, (S, O,) or it is an inf. n. syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqobN","text_ar":"عَقْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Efw","text_ar":"عفو"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one succeeded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took the place of, his father;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2098},{"kind":"text","text":"O, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eq~b","text_ar":"عقّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [Hence also several phrases here following.] ―         -b3-  It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~u gaAziyapK gazato yaEoqubu baEoDuhaA baEoDFA","text_ar":"كُلُّ غَازِيَةٍ غَزَتْ يَعْقُبُ بَعْضُهَا بَعْضًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Every party that goes forth on a warring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"warring and plundering, expedition"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall take its turn, one after another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] when one company has gone forth and returned, it shall not be constrained to go forth again until another has taken its turn after it. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqabotu Alr~ajula fiY A^aholihi","text_ar":"عَقَبْتُ الرَّجُلَ فِى اَهْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagayotuhu bi$ar~K waxalafotuhu","text_ar":"بَغَيْتُهُ بِشَرٍّ وَخَلَفْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I sought to do evil to the man, and took his place"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xlf","text_ar":"خلف"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with respect to his wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I committed adultery with his wife"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, O:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqabahu","text_ar":"عَقَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies [simply]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bigaAhu bi$ar~K","text_ar":"بِغَاهُ بِشَرٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sought to do evil to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K: [in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waxalafahu","text_ar":"وَخَلَفَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"seems to have been inadvertently omitted: but SM immediately adds what here follows:]) and one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqaba fiY A_ivori Alr~ajuli","text_ar":"عَقَبَ فِى اـِثْرِ الرَّجُلِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimaA yukorahu","text_ar":"بِمَا يُكْرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqobN","text_ar":"عَقْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He accused the man"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behind his back"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a thing disliked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hated; he"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defamed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"charged him with a vice"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fault"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqaba fulaAnN EalaY fulaAnapa","text_ar":"عَقَبَ فُلَانٌ عَلَى فُلَانَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalafa EalayohaA","text_ar":"خَلَفَ عَلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a man married such a woman after her first husband."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqaba Al$~ayobu","text_ar":"عَقَبَ الشَّيْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuquwbN","text_ar":"عُقُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whiteness of the hair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hoariness, came after"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took the place of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blackness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eq~b","text_ar":"عقّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqaba","text_ar":"عَقَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a horse, aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"text","text":"?], inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqobN","text_ar":"عَقْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which see below,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He performed a run after another run."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqabati AlA_ibilu mino makaAnK A_ilaY makaAnK","text_ar":"عَقَبَتِ الاـِبِلُ مِنْ مَكَانٍ اـِلَى مَكَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqobN","text_ar":"عَقْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEtqbt","text_ar":"اعتقبت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels removed from place to place, pasturing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqaba fiyhaA faEalayoka mino maAlika","text_ar":"عَقَبَ فِيهَا فَعَلَيْكَ مِنْ مَالِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Eaq~aba","text_ar":"مَا عَقَّبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the O, [in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY mAlk","text_ar":"فِى مالك"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn mAlk","text_ar":"من مالك"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whatever evil consequence happen"},{"kind":"text","text":"to me,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with respect to it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(referring to merchandise,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the responsibility"},{"kind":"text","text":"for it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will be on thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and compensation shall be made"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from thy property"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEoqibapN","text_ar":"تَعْقِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(thus in the O) appears, from what follows, to be an inf. n. of the latter verb in this sense; or it may perhaps be from the former verb, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taholikapN","text_ar":"تَهْلِكَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halaka","text_ar":"هَلَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAEaniY","text_ar":"بَاعَنِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siloEapF waEalayohi taEoqibapN A_ino kaAnat fiyhaA","text_ar":"سِلْعَةً وَعَلَيْهِ تَعْقِبَةٌ اـِنْ كَانَت فِيهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sold me an article of merchandise, and was responsible for an evil consequence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or for damage afterwards found in it,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"should there be any in it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (ISh, O, TA. *) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqabahu","text_ar":"عَقَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eq~bhu","text_ar":"عقّبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEqbhu","text_ar":"اعقبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"received, from him something in exchange, an exchange, a substitute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an equivalent, for another thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino lamo yaqoruwhu","text_ar":"اـِنْ لَمْ يَقْرُوهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falahu A^ano yaEoqubahumo bimivoli qiraAhu","text_ar":"فَلَهُ اَنْ يَعْقُبَهُمْ بِمِثْلِ قِرَاهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If they entertain him not. he shall have a right to take from them as a substitute the like of his entertainment"},{"kind":"text","text":"which they denied him: and one says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minohu xayorFA","text_ar":"مِنْهُ خَيْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstEqb","text_ar":"استعقب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~FA","text_ar":"شَرًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"received, from him in exchange good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqaba Alr~ajula","text_ar":"عَقَبَ الرَّجُلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took from the man's property the like of what he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the latter)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had taken from him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, * TA.) After the words in the Kur lx. 11,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA_ino faAtakumo $aYo'N","text_ar":"وَاـِنْ فَاتَكُمْ شَىْءٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino A^azowaAjikumo A_ilaY A@lokuf~aAri","text_ar":"مِنْ اَزْوَاجِكُمْ اـِلَى ا@لْكُفَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", there are three different readings, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEaAqabotumo","text_ar":"فَعَاقَبْتُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEaq~abotumo","text_ar":"فَعَقَّبْتُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEaqabotumo","text_ar":"فَعَقَبْتُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the first means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and ye take,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carry off, spoil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Masrook Ibn-El-Ajda', S, TA:) or the second has this meaning; and the first means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and ye punish them so that ye take,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carry off, spoil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the third means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and ye have a requital:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the second is the best; and the third is also good; but the second has a more intensive meaning: (Aboo-Is-hák the Grammarian, L, TA:) accord. to Fr, the first and second signify the same: (L, TA:) and As says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqobN","text_ar":"عَقْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqaba","text_ar":"عَقَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqaAbN","text_ar":"عِقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAqaba","text_ar":"عَاقَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but whether with reference to this case, I do not find]. (TA.) ―         -b11-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqaba","text_ar":"عَقَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqobN","text_ar":"عَقْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sought after, wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"some other thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqaba","text_ar":"عَقَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqobN","text_ar":"عَقْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bound"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the kind of sinew,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendon, called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqab","text_ar":"عَقَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eq~b","text_ar":"عقّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEoqiybN","text_ar":"تَعْقِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which see an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSonaEN","text_ar":"مَصْنَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he bound therewith"},{"kind":"text","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xawoq","text_ar":"خَوْق"},{"kind":"text","text":". i. e. the ring of an ear-drop, fearing lest it should incline on one side: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he bound"},{"kind":"text","text":"an earring"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a thread called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqaAb","text_ar":"عُقَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and he wound round"},{"kind":"text","text":"a bow, (S, O, K,) and an arrow, (S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the kind of sinew,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendon, called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqab","text_ar":"عَقَب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with somewhat thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqabahu biAlEaqabi","text_ar":"عَقَبَهُ بِالعَقَبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he bound it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, the [arrow termed]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qidoH","text_ar":"قِدْح"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqab","text_ar":"عَقَب"},{"kind":"text","text":", in consequence of its having broken. (IB, L, TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqabonaA Alr~akiy~apa","text_ar":"عَقَبْنَا الرَّكِيَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[thus I find it written without teshdeed, but perhaps it should be ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaq~abonaA","text_ar":"عَقَّبْنَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoqaAbu AlT~aY~","text_ar":"اَعْقَابُ الطَّىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqibN","text_ar":"عَقِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We lined the well with stones behind"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the other"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stones."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See also 4.])       -A4-  [The inf. n.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaqobu","text_ar":"العَقْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajoEu","text_ar":"الرَّجْعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which generally means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The making,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"causing, to return,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"go back;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this may perhaps be a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ujuwEu","text_ar":"الرُّجُوعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for it is immediately added,] Dhu-rRummeh says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kaA^an~a SiyaAHa Alkudori yanoZurona EaqobanaA\n                      \n                     \n                        taraATunu A^anobasATK Ealayohi TagaAmi"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"As though the crying of the dusky"},{"kind":"text","text":"she-camels]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"looking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waiting, for our returning"},{"kind":"text","text":"from watering that they might go to the water after us ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"were the barbarous talk of low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ignoble, Nabathæans, over it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. over the water]. (TA.)       -A5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqiba Aln~abotu","text_ar":"عَقِبَ النَّبْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqabN","text_ar":"عَقَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The branches of the plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage, became slender, and the leaves thereof turned yellow."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA. [See also 2.])"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","TK","Mgh","Msb","O","L"]},{"entry_id":"n29837","headword_ar":"عُقْبَةٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqibN","text_ar":"عَقِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last that remains:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN Euqobapu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ عُقْبَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baniY fulaAnK","text_ar":"بَنِى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the last that remains of the sons of such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A turn;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time at which,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"during which, anything is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is to be, done,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had, in succession:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqabN","text_ar":"عُقَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tam~ato","text_ar":"تَمَّتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euqobatuka","text_ar":"عُقْبَتُكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thy turn is completed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArato","text_ar":"دَارَتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euqobapu fulaAnK","text_ar":"عُقْبَةُ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The turn of such a one came round."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba EuqobapF","text_ar":"رَكِبَ عُقْبَةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rode one turn:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba Euqobatahu","text_ar":"رَكِبَ عُقْبَتَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rode his turn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his turn."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano ma$aY Eano","text_ar":"مَنْ مَشَى عَنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAb~atipi EuqobapF falahu ka*aA","text_ar":"دَابَّتِةِ عُقْبَةً فَلَهُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whoso walks a turn to a certain point, instead of his beast, to him shall be given such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euqobapu AlA^jiyri","text_ar":"عُقْبَةُ الاجِيرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hired-man's turn to ride; when the hirer dismounts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for example in the morning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and he"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the former"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rides."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) And [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqabN","text_ar":"عُقَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means [particularly] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turns of camels, when they are being watered:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the watering of a number of camels together after another number is termed their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euqobap","text_ar":"عُقْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqobaY","text_ar":"عُقْبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  And [it is said that] it means also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Camels which a man pastures and waters in his turn;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and IAar cites as an ex."},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_in~a EalaY~a EuqobapF A^aqoDiyhaA\n                      \n                     \n                        lasotu binaAsiyhaA walaA munosiyhaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but this I would rather render,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily I have incumbent on me a turn"},{"kind":"text","text":"to pasture and water camels;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and I perform it; I am not a neglecter thereof nor a delayer of it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning I drive the camels which I pasture and water in my turn, and I tend them well:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munosiyhaA","text_ar":"مُنْسِيهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munosiy^ihaA","text_ar":"مُنْسِيِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", for the sake of the rhyme. (TA.) ―         -b5-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place in which one mounts a beast to ride"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his turn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b6-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"space, of two leagues;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twice the distance termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farosax","text_ar":"فَرْسَخ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distance to which one journeys"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from one halting-place to the next;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a stage of a journey"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: pl. as above: a poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"xawodFA DinaAkFA laA tasiyru AlEuqabaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender, heavy in the hinder part, that will not perform men's marches"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning that she will not [or cannot] journey with men, because she will not endure the doing so on account of her soft and delicate life. (TA.) ―         -b7-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"space, between the ascending and descending"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a bird. (S, O, K.) ―         -b8-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"night"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"day;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because they follow each other. (K.) ―         -b9-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A substitute;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing that is given,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taken, in exchange for another thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, L, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqobaY","text_ar":"عُقْبَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*otu mino A^asiyriY EuqobapF","text_ar":"اَخَذْتُ مِنْ اَسِيرِى عُقْبَةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I took,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"received, for my captive, a substitute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"something in exchange."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saA^uEoTiyka minohaA EuqobaY","text_ar":"سَاُعْطِيكَ مِنْهَا عُقْبَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in a trad., meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will give thee something in exchange"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for her,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.] for sparing her life,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2102},{"kind":"text","text":"and liberating her. (L, TA.) ―         -b10-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pasture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an ostrich,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is eaten after other pasture"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and likewise of camels: and of men:] pl. as above. (AA, S, O.) One says of camels,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raEato EuqobatahaA","text_ar":"رَعَتْ عُقْبَتَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They pastured upon the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of plants termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xul~ap","text_ar":"خُلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, L;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xul~ap","text_ar":"خُلَّة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) and of men one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akaluwA Euqobatahumo","text_ar":"اَكَلُوا عُقْبَتَهُمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They ate their repast of sweetmeat after the other food."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA. [See 8, near the beginning.]) ―         -b11-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remains of the contents"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a cooking-pot,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adhering to the bottom."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Somewhat of broth which the borrower of a cooking-pot returns when he returns the pot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) ―         -b12-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Euqobapa","text_ar":"اُمُّ عُقْبَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cooking-pot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Am","text_ar":"ام"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abow Euqobapa","text_ar":"اَبْو عُقْبَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a surname of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hog."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 663. [But the origin of this I know not.]) ―         -b13-  One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytu minohu","text_ar":"لَقِيتُ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euqobapa AlS~unoEi","text_ar":"عُقْبَةَ الصُّنْعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I experienced from him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, difficulty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though lit. signifying,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the result of the deed"},{"kind":"text","text":"that I had done:] and [simply]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiYa minohu EuqobapF","text_ar":"لَقِىَ مِنْهُ عُقْبَةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He experienced from him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, difficulty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [But in a copy of the A, and in my opinion correctly, the last word in this phrase is written ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqabapF","text_ar":"عَقَبَةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqabapN","text_ar":"عَقَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.]) ―         -b14-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kunotu mar~apF nu$obap waA^anaA Alyawoma Euqobap","text_ar":"كُنْتُ مَرَّةً نُشْبَة وَاَنَا اليَوْمَ عُقْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", expl. by IAar as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was such that, when I clung to a man, he experienced evil from me; but now I have reverted from being such, through weakness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [It is a prov., somewhat differently related in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n$b","text_ar":"نشب"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]) ―         -b15-  See also the next paragraph, in four places."}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","O","Msb","K","L"]},{"entry_id":"n29838","headword_ar":"عِقْبَةٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, S, O, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqobapN","text_ar":"عُقْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, O, K,) but the former is the more approved, (Lh, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eqb","text_ar":"عقب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the TA, [app., if not a mistranscription, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqibN","text_ar":"عَقِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mark, sign, trace, impress, characteristic,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outward indication."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, S, O, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi Eiqobapu Als~arowi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ عِقْبَةُ السَّرْوِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euqobatuhu","text_ar":"عُقْبَتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljamaAli","text_ar":"الجَمَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Upon him is the mark"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of generosity and manliness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of beauty"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiqobapu Alqamari","text_ar":"عِقْبَةُ القَمَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqobapu","text_ar":"عَقْبَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqmr","text_ar":"القمر"},{"kind":"text","text":"mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The return of the moon, when it has set,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disappeared, and then risen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the return of the moon after the change;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA yafoEalu *`lika A_il~aA Eiqobapa Alqamari","text_ar":"مَا يَفْعَلُ ذٰلِكَ اـِلَّا عِقْبَةَ القَمَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euqobapa","text_ar":"عُقْبَةَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqmr","text_ar":"القمر"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the O,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He does not that save once in each month:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) but, accord. to IAar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqamari","text_ar":"القَمَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euqobapu","text_ar":"عُقْبَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm, is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain star,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asterism, which is in conjunction with the moon once in the year;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euqobapa Alqamari","text_ar":"عُقْبَةَ القَمَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"once in the year:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the following verse, of one of the Benoo-'Ámir:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"laA yuToEimu Almisoka waAlkaAfuwra lim~atahu\n                      \n                     \n                        walaA Al*~ariyrapa A_il~aA Euqobapa Alqamari"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He will not apply to his hair that descends below the ear musk and camphor, nor the perfume called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ryrp","text_ar":"ذريرة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"save once in the year"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or, as Lh relates it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiqobapa Alqmr","text_ar":"عِقْبَةَ القمر"},{"kind":"text","text":": thus in the L; in which it is added that this saying of IAar requires consideration, because the moon cuts [a meridian of] the celestial sphere once in every month: but MF replies that it may be in conjunction with the said star only once in the year, as the moon's path varies in each successive month. (TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqomapN","text_ar":"عَقْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqobapN","text_ar":"عَقْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Lh","S","O","K","TA","L"]},{"entry_id":"n29839","headword_ar":"عَقَبَةٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mountain-road;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a road in"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mountain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xc. 11:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a road in the upper part of a mountain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 287:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a difficult place of ascent of the mountains:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a mountain"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or [it sometimes signifies]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long mountain that lies across the way, and over which the way therefore leads; long,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"high, and very difficult; so called, too, when it is further impassable after it is ascended; rising high towards the sky, ascending and descending; most difficult of ascent; but sometimes its height is one"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uniform"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and its acclivity is in appearance like a wall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [generally it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a road over,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over some part of, a mountain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqaAbN","text_ar":"عِقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, Msb, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiqotaHama AlEaqabapa","text_ar":"اِقْتَحَمَ العَقَبَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He attempted the mountain-road"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is metaphorically used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He entered upon a hard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficult, affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xc. 11.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqobapN","text_ar":"عُقْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", near the end. ―         -b2-  It is also n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqabN","text_ar":"عَقَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S, O.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Msb","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}